                                      muKern v.0.1.062026

A minimal microkernel design for x86_64, ARMv8-A and RV64, 
plus a working proof-of-concept that boots on all three
and drops you into a tiny serial REPL.

USAGE

Toolchain setup (rootless container) is in INSTALL file. Once the
cross compilers and QEMU are available:

    $ make all              # build all three kernels
    $ make run-x86_64       # boot in QEMU (-nographic)
    $ make run-arm64
    $ make run-riscv64

Quit QEMU with Ctrl-A then x.

muKern ships with a minimal REPL commande line

---
    SeaBIOS (version 1.16.3-debian-1.16.3-2)
    iPXE (https://ipxe.org) 00:03.0 CA00 PCI2.10 PnP PMM+06FCAE00+06F0AE00 CA00
                                                                               
