NOTES

Each targets uses a different load address and boot path,

| arch    | boot path                          | UART                 | load addr  |
|---------|------------------------------------|----------------------|------------|
| x86_64  | Multiboot1 to long-mode trampoline | 16550 @ 0x3F8        | 1 MiB      |
| arm64   | QEMU virt ELF entry (EL1)          | PL011 @ 0x9000000    | 0x40080000 |
| riscv64 | OpenSBI to S-mode payload          | NS16550 @ 0x10000000 | 0x80200000 |

The x86_64 kernel is linked as ELF64 and re-wrapped to `elf32-i386`
with `objcopy` so QEMU's Multiboot loader accepts it; the machine code
is unchanged.
